1 The inclusion of this explanation does not constitute agreement with
2 the explanation’s substance by the members of the general assembly.
3 This bill relates to school safety by requiring the creation
4 of threat assessment teams and authorizing information sharing
5 between certain governmental agencies.
6 The bill allows covered entities that provide services to
7 students enrolled in kindergarten through grade 12 who are
8 experiencing or at risk of an emotional disturbance or mental
9 illness, or who pose an articulable and significant threat
10 to the health and safety of any person, to share records or
11 information that are reasonably necessary to ensure access to
12 appropriate services for such students, or to ensure the safety
13 of such students or others, with any other such covered entity.
14 The bill authorizes all such covered entities to communicate,
15 collaborate, and coordinate efforts to best serve students.
16 The bill defines “covered entity” to include nonpublic schools,
17 charter schools, innovation zone schools, the judicial branch,
18 a criminal or juvenile justice agency, political subdivisions,
19 state agencies, and any service or support provider that
20 contracts with such persons.
21 The bill authorizes school districts, accredited nonpublic
22 schools, charter schools, and innovation zone schools to
23 establish a multidisciplinary threat assessment team. The
24 multidisciplinary threat assessment team is required to
25 coordinate resources and assess and intervene when a student
26 enrolled in the school exhibits behavior that may pose a
27 threat to the safety of the school, school employees, or
28 other students enrolled in the school. The bill establishes
29 the membership of the multidisciplinary threat assessment
30 team. The bill authorizes school districts to enter into an
31 agreement with another school to create a multidisciplinary
32 threat assessment team that covers both schools. The bill
33 also authorizes multidisciplinary threat assessment teams to
34 share records or information in accordance with the bill’s
35 provisions. The bill provides immunity from civil liability
